{"type": "assistant", "uuid": "afbba34f-b307-5815-b569-c7a3815967f4", "timestamp": "2026-01-31T20:01:45.000Z", "sessionId": "2b8d2b9b-4baa-5578-ba88-f27022e89926", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "The Rust version compiles and passes all tests:\n\n```rust\npub fn find_duplicates(items: &[&str]) -> Vec<&str> {\n    use std::collections::HashMap;\n    let mut counts: HashMap<&str, usize> = HashMap::new();\n    for &item in items {\n        *counts.entry(item).or_insert(0) += 1;\n    }\n    let mut dupes: Vec<&str> = counts\n        .into_iter()\n        .filter(|(_, c)| *c > 1)\n        .map(|(k, _)| k)\n        .collect();\n    dupes.sort_unstable();\n    dupes\n}\n```\n\n`sort_unstable` gives deterministic output without the allocation overhead of stable sort. Let me know if you need the owned-`String` version."}], "model": "claude-sonnet-4-5", "usage": {"input_tokens": 6594, "output_tokens": 1591, "cache_creation_input_tokens": 0, "cache_read_input_tokens": 0}}}
